<br>
For example, at the last Fear raid:<br>
<br>
I organized, led it.<br>
Hareq lead tactics/master loot<br>
Telivak organized groups<br>
<br>
This needs to be done at every raid.  No one can do it theirselves.<br>
<br>
-Tekkang <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/19/01 9:44:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HATE: My recent experience and observations!</span><hr size=1> Sorry if I didnt make myself clear. I was NOT condemming any raids we have done or how they were handled. I was NOT saying the SE corner of the zone in building (which is the SE corner of the zone) is the only or even the best place to break Hate. As far as splitting leadership jobs, Tekkang is right, that is the way we do it. I was just restating our method. The raid I was on did it differently and had some trouble with loot dispersal, IMO. One person was doing several jobs and confusion on loot occured.<br>
<br>
I was NOT saying we should break Hate in the SE corner. I personally think the SW corner, or the Arch just north of there is a better idea. My only reservation with the SW break is how do we get to the SW corner? We used to head out the the zonein building make an immediate right turn, run up to the top of the wall, turn right and run to SE corner, then turn right and run to SW corner, then turn right and run a little ways to just above the arch. The reason we took this route is to lower chances of aggro. Running along the top of the wall kept us as far as possible away from mobs. Everything I have heard makes me believe running along the top of the wall can aggro mobs above and lead to serious trouble. I think the current plan is to take the same route and run along the middle of the wall. This will require alot of displine and I am not sure we can pull it off. Also this brings us very close to the imps in the SW corner and if they see invisible I think we will aggro them. The middle of the wall run seems the best plan at this point; but maybe others will respond to this post that know of a better way?<br>
<br>
Sorry if my post seemed to be flaming anyone. It was meant as information that might be useful, not as a recrimination.<br>
<br>
Myriah<br>
<br>
P.S. I didnt post this in the Hate raid area, because it was meant to be more general. Not about the upcoming raid; but multi-group raids in general, with some specifics about the Last Hate raid I was on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=boofa>Boofa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Retired Grand Poohbah of Amnesty</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/20/01 5:22:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HATE: My recent experience and observations!</span><hr size=1> Thanks Myria!<br>
